Note:
ORDERED MAP - Insertion-Order Preserving HashMap Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements an OrderedMap by overlaying a doubly-linked list
on top of a chained hash table. Each entry carries forward/backward
pointers in addition to its hash chain pointer, so iteration in
insertion order is O(n) (no sort step) while lookup remains O(1) average.

Entry structure (48 bytes):
  offset 0:  key (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 16: hash chain next (8 bytes)
  offset 24: order list prev (8 bytes)
  offset 32: order list next (8 bytes)
  offset 40: hash (8 bytes; cached for resize)

OrderedMap header (48 bytes):
  offset 0:  buckets (pointer to bucket array of capacity entries)
  offset 8:  capacity (power of two)
  offset 16: count
  offset 24: order_head (first inserted, still present)
  offset 32: order_tail (most recently inserted)
  offset 40: seed (hash seed)
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Let OMAP_ENTRY_SIZE be 48
Let OMAP_HEADER_SIZE be 48
Let OMAP_INITIAL_CAPACITY be 16

@Reasoning
Hash an integer key to a bucket index using splitmix64-style mix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same mix routine as hashmap.runa, kept inline so this file does not
depend on hashmap.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-cryptographic.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_hash" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let h be key
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 18397679294719823053
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    Set h to h multiplied by 14181476777654086739
    Set h to h bitwise xor (h shifted right by 33)
    If h is less than 0:
        Set h to 0 minus h
    End If
    Return h
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a new entry with prev/next/chain pointers zeroed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
48-byte alloc, fields set.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 48 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_entry_create" takes key as Integer, value as Integer, hash as Integer returns Integer:
    Let entry be proc allocate from Layout with OMAP_ENTRY_SIZE
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 0, key
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 8, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 40, hash
    Return entry
End Process

@Reasoning
Create empty OrderedMap.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate header + bucket array (zero-init for null bucket heads).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_create" returns Integer:
    Let om be proc allocate from Layout with OMAP_HEADER_SIZE
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets_bytes be OMAP_INITIAL_CAPACITY multiplied by 8
    Let buckets be proc allocate from Layout with buckets_bytes
    If buckets is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with om
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than buckets_bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with buckets, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 0, buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 8, OMAP_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 40, 2654435761
    Return om
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy ordered map. Walks the insertion-order list freeing each
entry (which incidentally visits every entry exactly once with no
duplicates because each entry sits in exactly one bucket chain).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk from order_head following next pointers, freeing each entry.
Then free buckets, then header.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_destroy" takes om as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 24
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 32
        proc deallocate from Layout with cur
        Set cur to next
    End While
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 0
    If buckets is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with buckets
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with om
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Find existing entry by key. Walks the bucket chain.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Compute hash and bucket index = hash AND (capacity - 1).
2) Walk the bucket chain comparing key fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_find_entry" takes om as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc omap_hash with key
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let ck be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If ck is equal to key:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Resize buckets to 2x capacity, rebucketing every entry. Insertion-order
linked list is unchanged because each entry's order pointers do not
depend on bucket index.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Allocate new bucket array (zero-init).
2) Walk insertion-order list; for each entry recompute new bucket and
   prepend to new bucket chain.
3) Free old bucket array.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n + new_capacity).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_resize" takes om as Integer returns Integer:
    Let old_buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 0
    Let old_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 8
    Let new_capacity be old_capacity multiplied by 2
    Let new_bytes be new_capacity multiplied by 8
    Let new_buckets be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
    If new_buckets is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than new_bytes:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with new_buckets, zi, 0
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While
    Let new_mask be new_capacity minus 1
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 24
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let next_in_order be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 32
        Let h be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 40
        Let new_idx be h bitwise and new_mask
        Let head_addr be new_buckets plus (new_idx multiplied by 8)
        Let existing_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 16, existing_head
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, cur
        Set cur to next_in_order
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with old_buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 0, new_buckets
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 8, new_capacity
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Insert or update. If the key exists, update value (insertion order
unchanged). Otherwise append a new entry to the order list and prepend
to the bucket chain.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If load >= 75%, resize.
2) Find existing entry; if found, set value, return 1.
3) Else allocate new entry, link into bucket chain head, link into
   order list at the tail, increment count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_set" takes om as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 16
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 8
    Let threshold be (capacity multiplied by 75) divided by 100
    If count is greater than or equal to threshold:
        Let r be proc omap_resize with om
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let existing be proc omap_find_entry with om, key
    If existing is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with existing, 8, value
        Return 1
    End If
    Let h be proc omap_hash with key
    Let entry be proc omap_entry_create with key, value, h
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 0
    Let new_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 8
    Let mask be new_capacity minus 1
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let existing_head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 16, existing_head
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, entry
    Let old_tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 32
    If old_tail is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 24, entry
    Otherwise:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with old_tail, 32, entry
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with entry, 24, old_tail
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 32, entry
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 16, count plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Lookup value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Find entry; return value field if found.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_get" takes om as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entry be proc omap_find_entry with om, key
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if find_entry returns non-zero.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_contains" takes om as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entry be proc omap_find_entry with om, key
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Remove key, unlinking from both bucket chain and order list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Find entry. If not found return 0.
2) Walk bucket chain again to find prev pointer in chain; splice.
3) Unlink from order list (handling head/tail cases).
4) Free entry, decrement count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) average.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if not present.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_remove" takes om as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buckets be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 0
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 8
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let h be proc omap_hash with key
    Let idx be h bitwise and mask
    Let head_addr be buckets plus (idx multiplied by 8)
    Let prev be 0
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let ck be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
        If ck is equal to key:
            Let next_chain be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
            If prev is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with head_addr, 0, next_chain
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with prev, 16, next_chain
            End If
            Let order_prev be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 24
            Let order_next be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 32
            If order_prev is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 24, order_next
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with order_prev, 32, order_next
            End If
            If order_next is equal to 0:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 32, order_prev
            Otherwise:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with order_next, 24, order_prev
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with cur
            Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 16
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with om, 16, count minus 1
            Return 1
        End If
        Set prev to cur
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Size accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read count field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_size" takes om as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
First (oldest insertion) entry pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Return order_head field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_first" takes om as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Last (most recent insertion) entry pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Return order_tail field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_last" takes om as Integer returns Integer:
    If om is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with om, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Next entry in insertion order following 'entry'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns the order-next pointer field at offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_entry_next" takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Key of entry pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_entry_key" takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Value of entry pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "omap_entry_value" takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry, 8
